<font color="#FF0000">WAR AND PEACE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Mar  7 22:39:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
     The history of man is a history of violence.  Reas the Old Testament---it's full of war, and war without rules, I might add.<br>
     Wishing or prayer won't stop war any more then laws will prevent crime.  As long as a indavidual or a nation want what someone else has, there will be crimes and war.<br>
   It does no good just too complan about how horrible war is---again, it's all in the Old Testiment and has been said by people ever since--and the wars continue.  Get used to it---shit happens--all the damn time.<br>
    There are two things we as a nation can do: work to prevent wars from happening--as we are trying to do in Bosnia and concurrently, prepare to win any war we are forced into.  The second is not beiing done at this time very well I am afraid.  That is unfortunate, since the best way to prevent war and &quot; fear no evil&quot;  is to be the strongest SOB &quot;in the valley...&quot;<br>
     As far as &quot;winning&quot; in Viet Nam, of course it was possible.  To try to argue that a nation that defeated Germany and Japan, couldn't have won against a third world armed force is ridiculous---from a military point of view!  The myth of the NVA carrying on in the forrest is just that--a myth.  We would simply have destroyed the forrest and what would they have eaten anyway.  <br>
   We simply didn't feel that the sacrafices needed were woth the goal.  And it wasn't, but that doesn't mean it couldn't have been accomplised.<br>
   Only one thing worse then fighting a war------and that's losing a war.<br>
Andy
